Package: genoformerR
Type: Package
Title: Ancestry-Aware Polygenic Risk Scoring via Transformer (GenoFormer)
Version: 0.3.1
Authors@R: person("Shu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "user@example.com")
Description: R wrapper for GenoFormer — a transformer-based ancestry-aware
    polygenic risk scoring pipeline using 1000 Genomes Phase 3 as ancestry
    reference. v0.3 provides a unified local ancestry dispatcher supporting
    FLARE (Java, no pre-phasing required, recommended), RFMix2 (legacy,
    requires SHAPEIT4 pre-phasing), and windowed PCA (pure R, no external
    tools or reference panel). All methods produce a (N x M x K) per-SNP
    posterior array for dual-level transformer conditioning: local ancestry
    fused into each SNP token, global ancestry via FiLM at every block.
    Python backend (PyTorch) managed via reticulate.
